column5: Did a solo trip today on Cedar Lake.Few fisherman at at Clarks and looks like some fly outs.Saw 8 boats today from clarks to cedar point resort as thats as far as I went.saw 4 muskies and hooked all 4 but only 2 in the bag and lost a huge one AGAIN.But had a great time.Landing muskies by yourself is pretty exciting.Toward the end of my day I put muskie gear away and pulled out my walleye rod to get some supper.Walleye bite is terrific añd there in alĺ depths so thinking there deep you might get disappointed.Burned through a couple of dozen minnows in no time.Again all nust eater size..Beautifull today so had to get out after the last few nasty days.Next week ill have lots of guide days so will hit more spots and see if I can find my guests bigger fish
The bigger the fish the bigger the money hahaha
At times!!!!you put people on big fish they should hand there wallet to you
I like the way you think.lol.
